WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.640
Michael Jordan.

00:04.640 --> 00:09.280
People in every country know that name.

00:09.280 --> 00:11.920
They know his face.

00:11.920 --> 00:17.080
They know his number, 23.

00:17.080 --> 00:20.760
He is tall and strong.

00:20.760 --> 00:24.000
He has a lot of money.

00:24.000 --> 00:27.760
He is very famous.

00:27.760 --> 00:32.040
And he can fly.

00:32.040 --> 00:36.400
Michael Jordan is a basketball player.

00:36.400 --> 00:43.080
He played for 13 years for the Chicago Bulls.

00:43.080 --> 00:47.440
Many people understand basketball.

00:47.440 --> 00:52.600
A lot of people love basketball.

00:52.680 --> 00:57.960
Michael Jordan lives basketball.

00:57.960 --> 01:03.080
Every game is important to him.

01:03.080 --> 01:06.240
But where did he come from?

01:06.240 --> 01:12.240
How did he win six NBA championships?

01:12.240 --> 01:17.000
When did he start to fly?

01:17.000 --> 01:20.160
Early days.

01:20.160 --> 01:26.800
Michael's story starts on February 17, 1963,

01:26.800 --> 01:30.160
in Brooklyn, New York.

01:30.160 --> 01:40.000
The family moves to Wilmington, North Carolina later in 1963.

01:40.000 --> 01:46.080
Michael is the son of Dolores and James Jordan.

01:46.080 --> 01:52.400
He comes from a happy home with a lot of love.

01:52.400 --> 02:00.800
One old friend says, The Jordan's door was always open.

02:00.800 --> 02:07.200
Mr. and Mrs. Jordan talked to us and listened to us.

02:07.200 --> 02:15.400
There was always a basketball game in the backyard.

02:15.400 --> 02:21.160
One Michael's best friend is his brother, Larry.

02:21.160 --> 02:28.200
Larry teaches his little brother a lot of things about basketball.

02:28.200 --> 02:36.560
Mr. Jordan builds a big basketball court for his sons and their friends.

02:36.560 --> 02:41.000
This is Michael's first basketball school.

02:41.480 --> 02:50.120
Today, Michael says, We played basketball games every day.

02:50.120 --> 02:56.280
On Saturdays, we were on our court all day.

02:56.280 --> 03:00.160
Rain? No problem.

03:00.160 --> 03:05.560
We played basketball.

03:05.640 --> 03:13.160
For a long time, Larry is the best basketball player in the Jordan family.

03:13.160 --> 03:17.040
Baseball is Michael's game.

03:17.040 --> 03:20.800
He is strong and quick.

03:20.800 --> 03:25.360
He always wants to win.

03:25.360 --> 03:34.160
The Jordan children have jobs at home, but Michael doesn't like working.

03:34.160 --> 03:39.520
His brothers and sisters have money for things.

03:39.520 --> 03:45.680
Michael doesn't have any money because he doesn't work.

03:45.680 --> 03:52.680
The only jobs in his life are baseball and basketball.

03:52.680 --> 03:56.760
Basketball at school.

03:56.760 --> 04:07.280
From 12 to 15 years old, Michael plays baseball, basketball, and football at school.

04:07.280 --> 04:11.120
He is short for a basketball player.

04:11.120 --> 04:19.600
He is only 1.75 meters, 5 feet, 9 inches.

04:19.600 --> 04:26.720
Mr. and Mrs. Jordan are under 1.75 meters.

04:26.720 --> 04:31.880
Michael isn't going to be very tall.

04:31.880 --> 04:39.920
In 1978, Michael starts his three years at Laney High School.

04:39.920 --> 04:46.520
His teachers say now, Michael was a good student.

04:46.520 --> 04:53.400
He was quiet, but he had a lot of friends.

04:53.400 --> 04:59.840
Michael starts basketball at Laney on the A team.

04:59.840 --> 05:04.200
Larry is on the A team too.

05:04.200 --> 05:08.320
He has number 45.

05:08.320 --> 05:21.200
Michael asks for number 23 because 45 divided by 2 equals 22 and a half.

05:21.200 --> 05:25.400
But Michael doesn't stay on the A team.

05:25.400 --> 05:30.240
The coach moves him to the B team.

05:30.240 --> 05:32.960
Michael is angry.

05:32.960 --> 05:36.600
He wants to be on the best team.

05:36.600 --> 05:43.960
He plays basketball every morning, afternoon, and evening.

05:43.960 --> 05:48.120
Sometimes he doesn't go to school.

05:48.120 --> 05:51.600
His father talks to him.

05:51.600 --> 05:59.200
Basketball is important, but school is important too.

05:59.200 --> 06:04.280
Michael goes back to school.

06:04.280 --> 06:08.600
It is the summer of 1979.

06:08.600 --> 06:15.840
Mr. Jordan remembers, Michael wanted to be tall.

06:15.840 --> 06:20.480
He wanted to be on the A team.

06:20.480 --> 06:30.120
Suddenly, he was 1.91 meters, 6 feet, 3 inches tall.

06:30.200 --> 06:35.880
In September, Michael plays on the A team.

06:35.880 --> 06:42.200
He is the star of basketball at Laney.

06:42.200 --> 06:48.120
The A team games start at 7.30 in the evening.

06:48.120 --> 06:54.720
Before 5 o'clock, the people of Wilmington are waiting at the court.

06:54.720 --> 06:58.720
They want to see Michael.

06:58.720 --> 07:04.840
Laney wins its first championship that year.

07:04.840 --> 07:07.960
College life.

07:07.960 --> 07:13.720
Now, Michael thinks about basketball after Laney.

07:13.720 --> 07:17.560
A lot of colleges want him.

07:17.560 --> 07:27.360
Michael likes the University of North Carolina, UNC in Chapel Hill.

07:27.360 --> 07:33.080
He likes the basketball coach, Dean Smith.

07:33.080 --> 07:42.000
Michael goes to UNC in September, 1981, with his sister Roslyn.

07:42.000 --> 07:49.640
She is a very good student, and she starts college early.

07:49.640 --> 07:56.840
Dean Smith teaches Michael a lot of things about basketball.

07:56.840 --> 08:04.640
Remember, every player on the team is important, he says.

08:04.640 --> 08:08.440
Michael works on his game.

08:08.440 --> 08:16.720
He is on the first team in his first year at UNC.

08:16.720 --> 08:25.720
Michael is the best new player in college basketball in 1981 to 2.

08:25.720 --> 08:36.480
The UNC team, the Tar Heels, get to the 1982 college basketball championships.

08:36.480 --> 08:41.640
They are going to play the Georgetown Hoyas.

08:41.640 --> 08:48.240
There are 61,000 people in New Orleans for the big game.

08:48.240 --> 08:55.440
It is Tar Heels, 61, Hoyas, 62.

08:55.440 --> 09:00.320
There is only a little time in the game now.

09:00.320 --> 09:08.320
Dean Smith says to his players, get the ball to Michael.

09:08.320 --> 09:12.040
Michael has the ball.

09:12.040 --> 09:19.360
The Hoyas run at him, but Michael doesn't look at the players.

09:19.360 --> 09:23.000
He looks at the basket.

09:23.000 --> 09:26.040
He takes a long shot.

09:26.040 --> 09:29.800
The ball is in the basket.

09:29.800 --> 09:37.440
UNC wins its first college championship.

09:37.440 --> 09:45.160
The story of The Shot is in the newspapers and on TV.

09:45.160 --> 09:48.080
Michael is Thanos.

09:48.080 --> 09:57.800
His photo and The Shot are on the Chapel Hill telephone book in 1982.

09:57.800 --> 10:06.600
The NBA, 1984 to 1993.

10:06.600 --> 10:13.840
Every year, the teams in the NBA look for good new players.

10:13.840 --> 10:23.200
After three important and happy years at UNC, Michael Jordan thinks about the NBA.

10:23.200 --> 10:32.080
But Dolores Jordan says to her son, finish your four years at UNC.

10:32.080 --> 10:36.160
It's very important.

10:36.160 --> 10:41.680
Michael says, I'm going to go to the NBA.

10:42.680 --> 10:49.040
But I'm going to finish my college work too.

10:49.040 --> 10:55.000
Michael finishes his work at UNC in 1986.

10:55.000 --> 10:59.880
His mother is very happy.

10:59.880 --> 11:09.000
In June of 1984, the NBA teams are looking for tall players.

11:09.000 --> 11:15.520
Michael is 1.98 meters, 6 feet, 6 inches.

11:15.520 --> 11:20.920
He isn't very tall for the NBA.

11:20.920 --> 11:32.840
The Houston Rockets take Hakim Alajuan, 2.08 meters, 6 feet, 10 inches.

11:32.840 --> 11:43.640
The Portland Trailblazers take Sam Bowie, 2.16 meters, 7 feet, 1 inch.

11:43.640 --> 11:50.080
Then, at number three, Jordan hears his name.

11:50.080 --> 11:53.760
The Chicago Bulls want him.

11:53.760 --> 11:59.280
The Bulls aren't a good team in 1984.

11:59.280 --> 12:13.440
They win only 27 of 82 games, but they give Michael $6 million for seven years.

12:13.440 --> 12:20.760
The Bulls always say to their players, you play for us now.

12:20.760 --> 12:24.880
No basketball on your vacations.

12:24.880 --> 12:29.160
This is your job.

12:29.160 --> 12:34.760
That Michael wants to play with his friends and with Larry.

12:34.760 --> 12:38.120
The Bulls want Michael.

12:38.120 --> 12:51.240
They say, OK Michael, you can play for us and you can play for the love of the game too.

12:51.240 --> 12:58.880
In July of 1984, Michael catches an airplane to Los Angeles.

12:58.880 --> 13:06.240
He is on the 1984 U.S. Olympic basketball team.

13:06.240 --> 13:11.760
The best college players in the country are on the team.

13:11.760 --> 13:19.120
They win their games and the Olympic award for basketball.

13:19.120 --> 13:24.040
Michael gives his award to his mother.

13:24.040 --> 13:31.840
He plays again and wins in the 1988 Olympic Games.

13:31.840 --> 13:39.560
After the 1984 Olympic Games, Michael starts his job with the Bulls.

13:39.560 --> 13:48.200
In the NBA, he can be a big star on the basketball court.

13:48.200 --> 13:53.720
Nike makes shoes for basketball players.

13:53.720 --> 14:00.120
Michael from Nike say, this new star can fly.

14:00.120 --> 14:05.000
He's going to be very famous.

14:05.000 --> 14:08.560
Nike makes a shoe for Michael.

14:08.560 --> 14:13.400
Its name is Air Jordan.

14:13.400 --> 14:23.560
Now Michael plays and people say, can he fly or is it the shoes?

14:24.280 --> 14:29.480
People buy a lot of Air Jordan shoes.

14:29.480 --> 14:36.920
In two years, Nike makes $130 million from them.

14:36.920 --> 14:42.360
Michael makes a lot of money from them too.

14:42.360 --> 14:45.640
Michael loves the NBA.

14:45.640 --> 14:49.000
His game is strong.

14:49.000 --> 14:52.520
People like watching him.

14:52.520 --> 14:58.600
But life away from the basketball court is often difficult.

14:58.600 --> 15:02.520
People always want to talk to him.

15:02.520 --> 15:06.120
Michael can't walk down the street.

15:06.120 --> 15:10.840
He can't go to a store or to a movie.

15:10.840 --> 15:14.600
People want to be his friend.

15:14.600 --> 15:21.240
In 1985, Michael meets Juanita Vanoy.

15:21.240 --> 15:26.760
She is smart and beautiful and interesting.

15:26.760 --> 15:31.480
But she doesn't know about basketball.

15:31.480 --> 15:36.840
She likes Michael because he is a good person.

15:36.840 --> 15:42.440
They want the same things in life.

15:42.440 --> 15:51.720
From 1984 to 1987, Michael wins a lot of awards in the NBA.

15:51.720 --> 15:57.400
But he wants to win the NBA championship.

15:57.400 --> 16:03.480
The newspapers ask, is Jordan a team player?

16:03.480 --> 16:09.400
Can the Bulls win the championship?

16:09.480 --> 16:15.960
From 1987 to 1990, the Bulls get some new players

16:15.960 --> 16:20.920
and a new coach, Bill Jackson.

16:20.920 --> 16:24.920
The Bulls start to build a championship team.

16:27.960 --> 16:35.240
In December 1988, there is a very happy story in the newspapers.

16:35.320 --> 16:39.800
Michael and Juanita have their first son.

16:39.800 --> 16:42.840
His name is Jeffrey.

16:42.840 --> 16:48.680
The 1990 to 1991 Bulls are very good.

16:48.680 --> 16:53.800
They win 61 of 82 games.

16:53.800 --> 17:00.760
The Bulls and the Los Angeles Lakers are in the championship games.

17:00.760 --> 17:07.080
The Bulls win the championship in five games.

17:07.080 --> 17:12.680
Michael says, we're a strong team.

17:12.680 --> 17:18.680
After seven years, we did it.

17:18.680 --> 17:23.480
Now, no team can stop the Bulls.

17:23.480 --> 17:31.240
They win the championship in 1992 and in 1993.

17:31.240 --> 17:36.600
The newspapers say, Michael Jordan is the best.

17:36.600 --> 17:42.280
He can win every game.

17:42.280 --> 17:49.080
Michael has many awards and three championships in three years.

17:49.080 --> 17:59.320
He and Juanita now have two sons, Jeffrey and Marcus and one daughter, Jasmine.

17:59.320 --> 18:07.240
After the championships in 1993, Michael goes home with his family.

18:07.240 --> 18:11.160
He is strong and happy.

18:11.160 --> 18:15.880
A new baseball star?

18:15.960 --> 18:22.280
Things are good for the Jordan family in the summer of 1993.

18:22.280 --> 18:28.920
But then, one day, Michael's father visits some friends.

18:28.920 --> 18:33.240
That evening, he doesn't come home.

18:33.240 --> 18:37.800
The police find him in a river.

18:37.800 --> 18:47.480
Two 18-year-old boys killed him for his car and his money.

18:47.480 --> 18:54.840
Michael loved his father very much and he can't understand this.

18:54.840 --> 19:01.720
Why did these boys kill a good man?

19:01.720 --> 19:10.280
On October 6, 1993, Michael and Juanita are on TV.

19:10.280 --> 19:16.040
Michael says, life is very short.

19:16.040 --> 19:21.480
I want to have time with my family.

19:21.480 --> 19:25.400
Michael retires from basketball.

19:25.400 --> 19:33.240
The Bulls retire his number, 23.

19:33.240 --> 19:40.120
Early in 1994, Michael starts a new job in baseball.

19:40.120 --> 19:49.080
Michael and a lot of young players try for a place on the Chicago White Sox baseball team.

19:49.080 --> 19:51.720
Michael can run well.

19:51.800 --> 19:54.200
He can catch well.

19:54.200 --> 19:58.520
But he can't hit a baseball very well.

19:58.520 --> 20:07.800
The newspapers say, Mike, please come back to basketball.

20:07.800 --> 20:11.560
But Michael likes playing baseball.

20:11.560 --> 20:15.880
In baseball, he isn't a star.

20:15.960 --> 20:19.400
Michael's number is 45.

20:19.400 --> 20:22.520
Larry's old number.

20:22.520 --> 20:31.000
But in August 1994, there are problems in baseball about money.

20:31.000 --> 20:34.600
The players stop the games.

20:34.600 --> 20:39.240
They don't play for a long time.

20:39.240 --> 20:43.240
Michael is 31 years old.

20:43.240 --> 20:47.800
He can't wait for baseball.

20:47.800 --> 20:54.840
The NBA 1995 to 8.

20:54.840 --> 21:04.840
On March 8, 1995, the Chicago Bulls office gives a story to the newspapers.

21:04.840 --> 21:09.000
It is a short story from Michael Jordan.

21:09.000 --> 21:14.280
It says, I'm back.

21:14.280 --> 21:20.840
Chicago is a very happy town that night.

21:20.840 --> 21:25.960
Michael is happy with the Bulls again and with his old friends

21:25.960 --> 21:29.640
and his coach, Phil Jackson.

21:29.640 --> 21:36.040
The team works well and starts to win again.

21:36.040 --> 21:42.040
Michael is number 45 in the championship games.

21:42.040 --> 21:46.360
The Bulls aren't doing very well.

21:46.360 --> 21:53.320
Some players say, number 45 is okay.

21:53.320 --> 21:58.440
But number 23 was a star.

21:58.440 --> 22:02.040
This makes Michael angry.

22:02.040 --> 22:06.440
He goes back to number 23.

22:06.440 --> 22:12.040
Now the players remember, he's back.

22:12.040 --> 22:18.120
The Bulls don't win the championship in 1995.

22:18.120 --> 22:22.760
In the summer, Michael has some time.

22:22.760 --> 22:27.720
He makes a movie, Space Jam.

22:27.720 --> 22:30.520
Children love it.

22:30.520 --> 22:35.000
It makes a lot of money.

22:35.000 --> 22:42.920
The Bulls start 1995 to 6 with a new player, Dennis Rodman,

22:42.920 --> 22:50.360
and some old players, Scotty Pippen and Michael Jordan.

22:50.360 --> 22:55.800
The Bulls are the best team in the NBA again.

22:55.800 --> 23:01.320
And Michael Jordan is their star.

23:01.320 --> 23:12.360
The Bulls win the NBA championship in 1996, 1997, and 1998.

23:12.360 --> 23:18.040
Michael Jordan has six NBA championship awards

23:18.040 --> 23:23.880
and he has basketball awards in every room in his house.

23:23.880 --> 23:28.040
But there are always problems in life.

23:28.040 --> 23:33.080
The Chicago Bulls office wants a new coach.

23:33.080 --> 23:38.520
But Michael Jordan likes playing for Phil Jackson.

23:38.520 --> 23:44.680
The NBA players are unhappy about their money too.

23:44.680 --> 23:51.000
They start the games late in 1998.

23:51.000 --> 23:56.680
Then Michael and Juanita are on TV again.

23:56.680 --> 24:05.000
Michael retires from basketball on January 13, 1999.

24:05.000 --> 24:11.880
He has good times and bad times in his first 36 years.

24:11.880 --> 24:20.680
But we remember Michael Jordan because he can fly.

24:20.760 --> 24:26.200
Michael has a lot of money from his life in basketball.

24:26.200 --> 24:34.520
In 2000, he buys an NBA team, the Washington Wizards.

24:34.520 --> 24:38.280
They aren't a good team.

24:38.280 --> 24:43.000
Michael Jordan isn't a player this time.

24:43.000 --> 24:46.760
It is his team.

24:46.840 --> 24:52.280
This is an interesting time for basketball.

24:52.280 --> 24:57.160
Is Michael Jordan's team going to fly?

